usage: main.py [-h]
               [--net {sbn,ssn,smn,vn,vn-linux,bcd,bct,bcp,gld,gl,imn,idn,itn}]
               [--list-nets] [--genesis-url GENESIS_URL]
               [--genesis-path GENESIS_PATH] [-s SEED] [--nodes NODES] [-v]
               [--web] [--debug] [--alerts] [--status] [--example] [--mlog]
               [--json [JSON [JSON ...]]] [--file [FILE [FILE ...]]]
               [--worksheet [WORKSHEET [WORKSHEET ...]]]

Fetch the status of all the indy-nodes within a given pool.

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --net {sbn,ssn,smn,vn,vn-linux,bcd,bct,bcp,gld,gl,imn,idn,itn}
                        Connect to a known network using an ID.
  --list-nets           List known networks.
  --genesis-url GENESIS_URL
                        The url to the genesis file describing the ledger
                        pool. Can be specified using the 'GENESIS_URL'
                        environment variable.
  --genesis-path GENESIS_PATH
                        The path to the genesis file describing the ledger
                        pool. Can be specified using the 'GENESIS_PATH'
                        environment variable.
  -s SEED, --seed SEED  The privileged DID seed to use for the ledger
                        requests. Can be specified using the 'SEED'
                        environment variable. If DID seed is not given the
                        request will run anonymously.
  --nodes NODES         The comma delimited list of the nodes from which to
                        collect the status. The default is all of the nodes in
                        the pool.
  -v, --verbose         Enable verbose logging.
  --web                 Start API server.
  --debug               Run in debug mode.
  --alerts              Alert Plug-in: Filter results based on alerts. Only
                        return data for nodes containing detected 'info',
                        'warnings', or 'errors'.
  --status              Status Only Plug-in: Get status only. Suppresses
                        detailed results.
  --example             Example Plug-in: Runs expample plug-in
  --mlog                Network Metrics Plug-in: Metrics log argument uses
                        google sheets api and requires, Google API Credentials
                        json file name (file must be in root folder), google
                        sheet file name and worksheet name. ex: --mlog --json
                        [Json File Name] --file [Google Sheet File Name]
                        --worksheet [Worksheet name]
  --json [JSON [JSON ...]]
                        Google API Credentials json file name (file must be in
                        root folder). Can be specified using the 'JSON'
                        environment variable.
  --file [FILE [FILE ...]]
                        Specify which google sheets file you want to log too.
                        Can be specified using the 'FILE' environment
                        variable.
  --worksheet [WORKSHEET [WORKSHEET ...]]
                        Specify which worksheet you want to log too. Can be
                        specified using the 'WORKSHEET' environment variable.
